would've happened?

14:31.500 --> 14:33.400
If I'm such a risk
to your child,

14:33.400 --> 14:34.533
then maybe you should
come home.

14:34.533 --> 14:36.033
I'll be there
in 20 minutes.

14:36.033 --> 14:37.766
(stammers, stunned)

14:39.166 --> 14:40.166
(beeps cell phone off)

14:40.166 --> 14:41.700
We have to go
straight to bed

14:41.700 --> 14:45.500
because your mother
has clearly lost her mind.

14:45.500 --> 14:46.400
Yeah.

14:47.633 --> 14:49.066
Oh, I know, Max.

14:53.433 --> 14:55.666
Okay, cave people
raised babies,

14:55.666 --> 14:58.600
so what if her kid's
a few minutes late for bed?

14:58.600 --> 15:01.166
It's not, it's not like
he can tell time.

15:01.166 --> 15:03.200
No, but you can.

15:03.200 --> 15:05.533
You were supposed to put him
down by seven, right?

15:05.533 --> 15:07.233
Um, whose side are you on?

15:07.233 --> 15:09.233
Mm, just the side
that makes me wonder:

15:09.233 --> 15:11.300
Is this really about
your friend's parenting style?

15:11.300 --> 15:12.666
Or is this about
something more?

15:12.666 --> 15:15.366
You know, right now is really
not the best moment

15:15.366 --> 15:17.733
