but we do need to talk.

15:17.733 --> 15:19.066
Hmm.

15:19.066 --> 15:19.700
What about?

15:19.700 --> 15:20.733
Kai?

15:20.733 --> 15:22.200
Kai.

15:22.200 --> 15:24.600
He's a patient, like me.

15:24.600 --> 15:26.300
May I?

15:26.300 --> 15:27.200
Knock yourself out.

15:27.200 --> 15:28.133
Oh, hello.

15:29.766 --> 15:32.066
Kai is going through
what I am.

15:32.066 --> 15:36.700
I finally met someone who's
doing the same thing and...

15:36.700 --> 15:38.766
He doesn't wanna talk
about it.

15:38.766 --> 15:41.700
I mean, isn't that weird?

15:41.700 --> 15:43.733
Erica, I'm not here
to gossip with you

15:43.733 --> 15:44.766
about other patients.

15:44.766 --> 15:47.033
In here,
we talk about you.

15:47.033 --> 15:49.166
That's it.

15:49.166 --> 15:52.766
So, third regret
from the bottom.

15:52.766 --> 15:53.766
Oh.

15:56.200 --> 15:57.566
Can we just talk about Kai?

15:57.566 --> 15:58.666
No.

15:58.666 --> 16:01.266
Tell me about frosh week.

16:02.600 --> 16:04.466
It was my second year,

16:04.466 --> 16:07.000
and I just moved in
with Ethan to a house

16:07.000 --> 16:08.100
with some other students,

16:08.100 --> 16:09.233
off campus.

16:10.533 --> 16:12.600
And Judith
and I were frosh leaders.

16:12.600 --> 16:14.533
At least,
we were supposed to be.

16:14.533 --> 16:17.033
At the end of first year
I signed us up

16:17.033 --> 16:18.600
and Judith,
she didn't even want to,

16:18.600 --> 16:24.333
but... I insisted
and then I bailed.

16:24.333 --> 16:26.733
See, I'd spent the summer

16:26.733 --> 16:29.133
reading women's theory

16:29.133 --> 16:31.500
and by the time
frosh week came,

16:31.500 --> 16:34.166
I really wanted to commit
myself to women's issues,

16:34.166 --> 16:37.666
so I whipped off my shirt
and marched around campus

16:37.666 --> 16:41.233
until I got
a major sunburn on...

16:41.233 --> 16:43.400
Much more dignified
than frosh week.

16:43.400 --> 16:46.733
Well, hey, if men can take their
shirts off on a hot day, then...

16:46.733 --> 16:48.200
I know.

16:48.200 --> 16:50.600
But it seemed to matter
at the time, it really did.

16:50.600 --> 16:53.166
And Judith?

16:53.166 --> 16:56.133
Erica: I left jude to manage
a massive group of frosh.

16:56.133 --> 16:57.166
Single-handed.

16:57.166 --> 16:59.700
30 kids away from home
for the first time,

16:59.700 --> 17:04.366
just drunk on freedom
and god knows what else.

17:04.366 --> 17:06.633
But good ol' Jude
she stuck it out

17:06.633 --> 17:07.766
even after I bailed.

17:09.500 --> 17:12.300
And she hated
every second of it.

17:15.033 --> 17:18.333
Ever since then there's been
this dynamic between us.

17:18.333 --> 17:21.366
Where she's the grown up
and I'm the flake.

17:21.366 --> 17:25.433
I can't even be trusted to
watch her son for a few hours.

17:25.433 --> 17:27.300
We're supposed to be
best friends, Dr. Tom,

17:27.300 --> 17:30.433
but I never see her anymore.

17:30.433 --> 17:33.000
Our friendship,
it's on life support.

17:33.000 --> 17:34.666
Well, sounds like
you should go back

17:34.666 --> 17:36.433
and resuscitate it.

17:39.466 --> 17:41.033
Judith:
This is what you do!

17:41.033 --> 17:42.333
I didn't know
it was possible

17:42.333 --> 17:43.666
to be this juvenile!

17:43.666 --> 17:46.200
I mean, you just follow
every whim and every--

17:46.200 --> 17:47.466
No-no-no-no, Judith,
Judith, it's okay,

17:47.466 --> 17:49.400
just take a deep breath,
okay?

17:49.400 --> 17:52.200
'cause I'm not doing feminist
frosh week anymore.

17:52.200 --> 17:53.333
I am staying with you.

17:53.333 --> 17:54.166
(Max cries)

17:58.033 --> 17:59.200
What is that?

17:59.200 --> 18:01.000
(Max whines loudly)

18:01.000 --> 18:01.600
Uh...

18:10.666 --> 18:12.233
Uh...

18:12.233 --> 18:14.733
Is this some kind
of frosh week hazing joke?

18:14.733 --> 18:16.533
You know,
I am not laughing.

18:16.533 --> 18:18.333
Trust me,
I am not either.

18:18.333 --> 18:20.500
Why are you baby-sitting
some kid?

18:20.500 --> 18:22.700
I'm baby-sitting.
Yes, I am!

18:22.700 --> 18:25.233
So, Judith,
meet little Max.

18:25.233 --> 18:26.333
Isn't he a cutie-pie?

18:26.333 --> 18:29.400
Mm. so you bail on doing
frosh week with me,

18:29.400 --> 18:31.700
but then one of your
girl power buddies needs help

18:31.700 --> 18:33.400
and you're all,
"Hey, no problem"!

18:33.400 --> 18:35.400
No-no-no, I'm not bailing
on you, okay, Judith.

18:35.400 --> 18:37.200
Change of plans;
I am there for you.

18:37.200 --> 18:38.533
And so is Max.

18:38.533 --> 18:40.300
I am steady as a rock.

18:40.300 --> 18:42.600
I just need five minutes
to go, um...

18:42.600 --> 18:45.166
And freshen up.
If you could just...

18:45.166 --> 18:48.400
Hold him and then
we're so froshing.

18:48.400 --> 18:50.566
You guys are really
cute together.

18:50.566 --> 18:51.300
(Max whines)

18:53.133 --> 18:55.633
You know I can't stand
these things, right?

18:55.633 --> 18:56.366
Erica!

18:57.600 --> 18:59.233
♪

18:59.233 --> 19:01.366
Where is your mother?

19:01.366 --> 19:06.333
♪

19:06.333 --> 19:08.333
You four, sign duty.
Go.

19:08.333 --> 19:09.666
You wash that car
over there.

19:09.666 --> 19:10.633
Everybody else just...

19:10.633 --> 19:13.133
Just grab a sponge
and just move on down.

19:13.133 --> 19:14.433
All right, move it, frosh!

19:14.433 --> 19:16.266
Shhh, it's okay,
it's okay.

19:16.266 --> 19:17.433
Judith:
So, uh, here,

19:17.433 --> 19:20.433
these buckets need filling
and soaping.

19:20.433 --> 19:21.566
Fast.

19:21.566 --> 19:22.666
Erica: Oh, hey, Judith,
would you just, um,

19:22.666 --> 19:24.433
would you mind
if just I supervised

19:24.433 --> 19:25.433
'cause he's kinda cranky.

19:25.433 --> 19:27.500
"I'm here for you,
Judith."

19:27.500 --> 19:29.300
Erica: totally am.
We're totally...

19:29.300 --> 19:31.333
We're here.
We're here, buddy.

19:34.666 --> 19:36.133
Hey.

19:36.133 --> 19:36.666
(Max whines)

19:38.200 --> 19:40.366
I know. it's okay,
it's okay.

19:44.133 --> 19:47.333
Oh, buddy, it's okay.
You're just tired.

19:47.333 --> 19:48.600
Oh. oh.

19:48.600 --> 19:50.066
It's okay.

19:50.066 --> 19:52.566
Oh, why don't I sing you
a song?

19:52.566 --> 19:55.000
Okay, baby songs,
baby songs.

19:55.000 --> 19:56.233
Uh...

19:56.233 --> 19:58.400
(singing)
♪ Little baby so cute ♪

20:00.300 --> 20:02.000
Oh baby.

20:02.000 --> 20:03.466
(whack)

20:03.466 --> 20:04.666
What the hell?!

20:04.666 --> 20:06.666
Judith: they're kids at
a carwash, Erica.

20:06.666 --> 20:07.400
Just...

20:08.666 --> 20:09.633
What reeks?

20:09.633 --> 20:12.400
I know, I just...
You know, two minutes.

20:13.700 --> 20:14.533
Okay.

20:21.466 --> 20:23.733
It's not so bad.
It's not so bad.

20:23.733 --> 20:24.400
Oh!

20:26.533 --> 20:29.366
(sputtered exhale,
disgusted)

20:29.366 --> 20:30.666
(diaper sloshes
onto roof of car)

20:30.666 --> 20:32.200
Oh crap!

20:32.200 --> 20:34.066
What is that on my car?

20:34.066 --> 20:35.666
Yeah, I'm really sorry
about that.

20:35.666 --> 20:37.533
Man: There's
shit on my car!

20:37.533 --> 20:39.300
Judith:
Okay, uh, sir?

20:39.300 --> 20:41.433
I am sorry,
my friend has problems.

20:41.433 --> 20:42.700
Judith, I...

20:42.700 --> 20:45.033
Just, just go.
okay.

20:45.033 --> 20:46.500
♪ Love me, love me ♪

20:46.500 --> 20:48.500
♪ Say that you love me ♪

20:48.500 --> 20:49.433
Okay.

20:50.500 --> 20:51.466
Um...

20:52.533 --> 20:53.533
I'm sorry.

20:53.533 --> 20:55.233
♪ Love me, love me ♪

20:55.233 --> 20:58.066
♪ Pretend that you love me ♪

20:58.066 --> 21:00.566
♪ I don't care
'bout anything but you ♪

21:04.233 --> 21:06.133
(makes playful
trilling sound)

21:06.133 --> 21:07.233
(cart rattles)

21:08.533 --> 21:09.300
Man: Miss?

21:11.466 --> 21:14.200
You do realize that
stealing a shopping cart

21:14.200 --> 21:15.200
is against the law?

21:15.200 --> 21:16.600
(half laughs)

21:16.600 --> 21:18.600
A: I'm borrowing it.

21:18.600 --> 21:20.433
And B:
you're unbelievable.

21:20.433 --> 21:22.666
And a disgrace to your uniform,
you know that?

21:22.666 --> 21:25.433
Wow, it's a lot of needs
for one small body, huh?

21:25.433 --> 21:27.266
Erica: Look, I came
here to show Judith

21:27.266 --> 21:29.266
that I am not a flake,
instead?

21:29.266 --> 21:30.700
I'm a baby-toting flake.

21:30.700 --> 21:32.433
Which, FYI,
is so much worse.

21:32.433 --> 21:34.433
I want this child back
where he belongs.

21:34.433 --> 21:36.633
I can't do what
I came here for.

21:36.633 --> 21:39.366
