I just don't understand why
you're flaking out on me and not

24:33.133 --> 24:34.200
on her?

24:34.200 --> 24:35.633
Jude, I know that's what
this looks like,

24:35.633 --> 24:37.733
and I promise it's not,
okay? I swear to you.

24:37.733 --> 24:39.233
Really, it's not?

24:39.233 --> 24:40.633
Why don't I believe you,
Erica?

24:40.633 --> 24:43.366
Look, I have a baby
that needs to go to bed

24:43.366 --> 24:46.133
and you yelling at me is not
making the situation better,

24:46.133 --> 24:47.733
and it is definitely
not helping him.

24:47.733 --> 24:49.033
Just go, okay?

24:49.033 --> 24:51.200
Just leave me here with
these frosh all by myself.

24:51.200 --> 24:53.133
I-I'll be fine.
Totally fine.

24:53.133 --> 24:56.666
♪ I've never known
a girl like you before ♪

24:56.666 --> 24:57.333
(Max cries)

24:59.033 --> 25:01.433
(Erica sings to Max,
Max cries)

25:05.366 --> 25:08.333
Okay,
I know you're not...

25:08.333 --> 25:09.633
You're not hungry,
you're tired.

25:09.633 --> 25:10.666
I know. I know.

25:12.133 --> 25:13.033
Judith:
Hey, guys!

25:13.033 --> 25:14.766
Not cool, no.

25:14.766 --> 25:16.433
No-no-no.
Oh, no-no-no.

25:16.433 --> 25:18.033
Oh, shit.

25:18.033 --> 25:20.233
(Max wails loudly)

25:20.233 --> 25:22.233
Please, please,
please go to bed, okay?

25:22.233 --> 25:24.533
I just, I just, I just
need one minute to...

25:24.533 --> 25:27.066
Okay, please?

25:27.066 --> 25:29.066
(chatter over police radio)

25:30.500 --> 25:33.366
(hairdryer whirs,
Erica gently shushes Max)

25:36.233 --> 25:39.033
What the hell
are you doing?

25:39.033 --> 25:40.300
What?!
Shhhh...

25:42.466 --> 25:44.500
I'm trying to pass out
here!

25:44.500 --> 25:46.033
No-no-no, listen,
there's no crying, okay?

25:46.033 --> 25:47.533
Wha-wha-wha-wha.
Please--

25:47.533 --> 25:49.700
You know, Ethan says to me,
"oh, I got this great girl,

25:49.700 --> 25:51.200
she's gonna be this
awesome roommate".

25:51.200 --> 25:52.400
And I'm thinking, "Okay."

25:52.400 --> 25:54.700
But really, I don't want
to live with chicks

25:54.700 --> 25:56.466
because chicks' lives
are too complicated.

25:56.466 --> 25:57.700
Just stop yelling at me!

25:57.700 --> 26:00.266
You know, you wanna pretend
that you're on Degrassi,

26:00.266 --> 26:03.033
where everybody loves
the spunky teen mom?

26:03.033 --> 26:05.066
Then live someplace else.

26:05.066 --> 26:06.600
Ethan: Michael, Michael.
Back off her, man.

26:06.600 --> 26:07.633
You know what?

26:07.633 --> 26:09.400
If the kid isn't
gone by tomorrow,

26:09.400 --> 26:10.500
then I am.

26:10.500 --> 26:13.766
Because I don't think
he pays rent.

26:13.766 --> 26:15.233
shhh.

26:15.233 --> 26:17.133
Oh, Ethan.

26:17.133 --> 26:19.666
Ethan,
thank you so much.

26:19.666 --> 26:21.433
Thank you for being
there for me.

26:21.433 --> 26:23.266
Uh, Erica,
look, I wanna help,

26:23.266 --> 26:26.133
but I'm so loaded right now,
I can barely stand.

26:26.133 --> 26:27.166
Please.

26:27.166 --> 26:28.533
I can't take care
of a baby.

26:28.533 --> 26:29.500
I'm sorry.

26:29.500 --> 26:31.300
Please.

26:32.633 --> 26:33.700
Shhh.

26:33.700 --> 26:35.733
No-no-no, it's okay.

26:35.733 --> 26:37.333
(mimics whirring)

26:41.633 --> 26:42.500
(birds chirp)

26:43.733 --> 26:44.766
Vroom!

26:44.766 --> 26:47.133
Bounce, bounce.

26:47.133 --> 26:48.733
Shh-shh.
Vroom.

26:48.733 --> 26:49.766
Please, Max.

26:49.766 --> 26:51.200
Bounce, bounce.

26:51.200 --> 26:53.266
Judith: Do you have any idea
what I've been doing all night?!

26:53.266 --> 26:55.100
Shh-shh, vroom.

26:55.100 --> 26:56.366
Bounce, bounce.

26:56.366 --> 26:58.133
Whoa, Erica, stop.

26:58.133 --> 27:00.466
Shh-shh,
vroom.

27:00.466 --> 27:01.333
What's wrong?

27:01.333 --> 27:02.466
Is something wrong with Max?

27:02.466 --> 27:03.666
Vroo- yup.

27:03.666 --> 27:05.600
No-no, if I don't do
the "bounce-bounce-shh-shh"

27:05.600 --> 27:09.100
and pat his bum
on every third, "vroom".

27:09.100 --> 27:10.233
If I don't...

27:10.233 --> 27:12.166
(Max cries)

27:12.166 --> 27:14.300
I know.
Whoa, whoa.

27:14.300 --> 27:17.033
You know what?
Enough, okay?

27:17.033 --> 27:18.566
You cannot go on
like this.

27:18.566 --> 27:20.266
I'm calling a cab.

27:20.266 --> 27:21.566
Cabs don't have
baby seats.

27:21.566 --> 27:24.033
That is the least
of your problems.

27:24.033 --> 27:27.200
(Erica repeats calming mantra
while Max cries wildly)

27:28.666 --> 27:30.666
(inhales and exhales)

27:33.566 --> 27:34.300
(Max cries)

27:37.033 --> 27:39.433
Erica: shh-shh-shh-shh,
shush-shush-shush.

27:39.433 --> 27:42.600
Where are we going?

27:42.600 --> 27:45.333
Your mom's.

27:45.333 --> 27:48.766
She'll know what
to do with you.

27:48.766 --> 27:50.500
Frosh week this time
last year,

27:50.500 --> 27:52.466
we were having
so much fun.

27:52.466 --> 27:53.700
Yes we were.

27:55.233 --> 27:57.000
Do you remember driving
into the fountain

27:57.000 --> 27:59.433
and then the cops
chasing us?

27:59.433 --> 28:00.433
Yup.

28:03.266 --> 28:06.300
So, how within a year

28:06.300 --> 28:09.333
could you dump me
for your feminist friends?

28:09.333 --> 28:11.300
I don't get it.

28:11.300 --> 28:13.300
Jude, I didn't dump you.

28:13.300 --> 28:16.533
Yes, you did, actually.

28:16.533 --> 28:19.500
Whatever, that seems to be
your specialty these days.

28:19.500 --> 28:20.333
Judith.

28:20.333 --> 28:22.366
Look, it is what it is,
you know?

28:22.366 --> 28:23.666
I just wish
I could understand

28:23.666 --> 28:25.366
why this woman
and her baby

28:25.366 --> 28:27.400
seem to be more important
to you than me.

28:27.400 --> 28:29.033
It's not that.
Yeah, it is!

28:29.033 --> 28:30.066
It's like...

28:30.066 --> 28:32.066
I don't even know
who you are anymore.

28:32.066 --> 28:33.266
Oh, come on!

28:33.266 --> 28:35.033
I am still the same person,
okay?

28:35.033 --> 28:37.400
I'm just trying to deal
with this situation.

28:37.400 --> 28:40.200
I know, I know, baby,
you just need sleep.

28:40.200 --> 28:43.500
What you need, Max,
is to go home.

28:43.500 --> 28:46.000
And what I need is some
patience and support.

28:46.000 --> 28:47.266
Oh god, here we go!

28:47.266 --> 28:49.366
Why does everyone act like
taking care of children

28:49.366 --> 28:50.700
is the hardest thing ever?

28:50.700 --> 28:51.533
(chuckles)

28:51.533 --> 28:52.600
Because you know what?

28:52.600 --> 28:53.766
It is.

28:53.766 --> 28:55.566
And you have no idea
what you're talking about.

28:55.566 --> 28:56.433
Wait. you know what?

28:56.433 --> 28:57.466
Judith, wait--

28:57.466 --> 28:59.066
Wait until you
have a baby.

28:59.066 --> 29:02.200
Yeah, fat chance,
me having a kid after today.

29:03.633 --> 29:04.566
Hmm.

29:09.033 --> 29:10.133
Samantha:
It's my hair.

29:10.133 --> 29:11.366
I know, honey.

29:11.366 --> 29:14.366
Stephanie says that Josh doesn't
get to tell me what to do with

29:14.366 --> 29:16.700
my hair and that I should
just cut it anyways.

29:16.700 --> 29:19.033
Well, Stephanie isn't Josh's
girlfriend, you are.

29:19.033 --> 29:21.000
A little lesson about men,

29:21.000 --> 29:23.300
they need to feel important.

29:23.300 --> 29:24.333
Stephanie says--

29:24.333 --> 29:26.366
I don't care what
Stephanie says,

29:26.366 --> 29:28.233
honey, it's just hair.

29:28.233 --> 29:31.566
When you love someone,
it's nice to make them happy.

29:31.566 --> 29:32.566
Erica?

29:32.566 --> 29:34.466
Hey, Sammy,
hey, Mom.

29:34.466 --> 29:38.300
What are you doing here
with a baby?

29:38.300 --> 29:41.366
I'm just baby-sitting
for a friend.

29:41.366 --> 29:42.366
Erica needs help.

29:42.366 --> 29:44.100
She needs some
experienced hands.

29:44.100 --> 29:47.233
Well,
I have a set of those.

29:47.233 --> 29:50.100
Come here little guy.

29:50.100 --> 29:51.066
Hello, handsome.

29:51.066 --> 29:52.000
Yes.

29:54.466 --> 29:56.166
Shhhh.

29:56.166 --> 29:57.500
Sleepy-sleepy-sleep.

29:57.500 --> 30:01.266
You're lucky the Salsberg's are
having a baby shower next week.

30:01.266 --> 30:04.166
I just pulled this out
of the gift basket

30:04.166 --> 30:06.333
and sterilized it,
and...

30:08.000 --> 30:09.633
Let the sleeping begin.

30:09.633 --> 30:11.633
His mom really doesn't
want me using those,

30:11.633 --> 30:13.133
I don't think
that we should.

30:13.133 --> 30:14.433
Did you turn out okay?

30:14.433 --> 30:16.633
'Cause you were hooked
on them.

30:16.633 --> 30:19.266
And I liked my sleep.

30:19.266 --> 30:21.466
Oh, god, so do I.

30:21.466 --> 30:23.300
I had no idea.

30:23.300 --> 30:24.500
I'm going to work.

30:24.500 --> 30:27.000
Promise me you'll call
the boy's mother.

30:27.000 --> 30:27.733
Today.

30:49.766 --> 30:51.266
Oh god.

30:52.533 --> 30:54.100
You want me to go in?

30:54.100 --> 30:55.300
No, no, it's fine,

30:55.300 --> 30:57.566
he's learning
to self-soothe.

30:57.566 --> 30:59.666
Thank you
for making me come here.

30:59.666 --> 31:02.400
Oh, who would leave
a crazy girl with a baby

31:02.400 --> 31:04.266
having a meltdown.

31:08.166 --> 31:11.400
See, we just need to give max
a few minutes to cool down.

31:11.400 --> 31:14.200
Oh, yeah, you needed
to give him a pacifier.

31:14.200 --> 31:16.100
Like, last night.

31:22.566 --> 31:24.366
You know,
this is the first time

31:24.366 --> 31:27.100
we've been alone together
since...

31:27.100 --> 31:29.033
Probably, last spring.

31:29.033 --> 31:30.233
What?

31:30.233 --> 31:31.233
No, that's not possible.

31:31.233 --> 31:33.733
Yeah, think about it.

31:33.733 --> 31:36.233
Back in high school,
we used to spend...

31:36.233 --> 31:38.466
Sometimes days together.

31:40.233 --> 31:41.566
Trust me,
ten years from now,

31:41.566 --> 31:43.366
we are still gonna
be hanging out

31:43.366 --> 31:45.200
and we're gonna laugh
at this time.

31:45.200 --> 31:47.233
You don't know that.

31:47.233 --> 31:48.633
What if we hit 30

31:48.633 --> 31:51.200
and you're, like,
some famous author

31:51.200 --> 31:53.733
and don't have anything
in common anymore?

31:53.733 --> 31:55.266
Not gonna happen.

31:55.266 --> 31:56.766
How do you know,
for sure?

31:56.766 --> 31:59.333
Because you're one of the most
important people in the world

31:59.333 --> 32:00.333
to me.

32:02.400 --> 32:04.400
You're my best friend.

32:11.366 --> 32:12.366
(laugh)

32:21.000 --> 32:22.033
(knock on door)

32:28.100 --> 32:30.566
Finally.

32:30.566 --> 32:32.133
It's quiet in here.

32:32.133 --> 32:34.466
Yeah,
everybody's sleeping.

32:34.466 --> 32:36.700
Judith is crashed out
on the couch

32:36.700 --> 32:38.766
and Max is over here.

32:38.766 --> 32:40.333
Come and see.

32:42.333 --> 32:44.166
My mom is getting
the biggest

32:44.166 --> 32:46.166
mother's day gift ever
this year.

32:46.166 --> 32:48.166
Not as easy as it looks,
huh?

32:48.166 --> 32:50.300
Erica: The amount of havoc that
little person caused?

32:50.300 --> 32:53.166
Unreal,
I had no idea.

32:53.166 --> 32:54.566
Neither did Judith.

32:54.566 --> 32:57.566
She had to give birth
on top of it.

32:57.566 --> 33:00.000
To have your life change
so radically?

33:00.000 --> 33:01.166
It's bewildering.

33:01.166 --> 33:03.133
Everything she was good at:

33:03.133 --> 33:05.266
litigation,
case law,

33:05.266 --> 33:07.166
lunching with clients,

33:07.166 --> 33:08.400
gone.

33:08.400 --> 33:09.333
(Max whines)

33:09.333 --> 33:11.233
And instead, chaos.

33:14.433 --> 33:17.766
Beautiful chaos,
but chaos.

33:17.766 --> 33:19.433
So, tell me something?

33:19.433 --> 33:22.533
What did you need the most

33:22.533 --> 33:25.300
when you had a baby
attached to you every moment?

33:27.666 --> 33:29.300
For people to understand.

33:29.300 --> 33:33.500
You know, to give max and
I room to figure it out.

33:33.500 --> 33:35.233
"Friendship is born
at that moment

33:35.233 --> 33:37.100
when one person says
to another,

33:37.100 --> 33:38.666
"What, you too?"

33:38.666 --> 33:40.633
"I thought I was
the only one."

33:40.633 --> 33:41.733
C.S. Lewis.

33:47.100 --> 33:48.033
(exhales)

33:52.100 --> 33:53.333
(door clicks open)

33:56.066 --> 33:58.266
Hey, I was wrong
and I am sorry.

33:58.266 --> 33:59.733
The whole sleeping thing,

33:59.733 --> 34:02.100
it matters a lot.

34:02.100 --> 34:03.466
You were right.

34:07.100 --> 34:08.400
Thank you.

34:08.400 --> 34:10.566
I mean, I didn't try hard
enough to understand

34:10.566 --> 34:13.366
where you were coming from.

34:13.366 --> 34:16.233
Well, it's really hard
if you haven't been there.

34:16.233 --> 34:18.266
How babies get when
they're overtired.

34:18.266 --> 34:19.266
Oh, I know.
'cause...

34:19.266 --> 34:21.066
Because I was talking
to a friend

34:21.066 --> 34:22.433
and she was telling me
stories.

34:22.433 --> 34:24.433
The deep knee bends,
and blow dryers,

34:24.433 --> 34:26.199
and the crazy lengths
she went through

34:26.199 --> 34:28.199
to get her baby
to go to bed.

34:28.199 --> 34:30.699
Well, I've been there.

34:30.699 --> 34:31.433
I bet.

34:34.566 --> 34:36.266
Is he sleeping?

34:44.066 --> 34:46.633
Oh, I miss him.

34:46.633 --> 34:48.633
Whenever I'm away from him,
I just start thinking.

34:48.633 --> 34:49.566
Ohhh...

34:52.666 --> 34:54.566
Is that a pacifier?

34:54.566 --> 34:56.433
Erica: I know, but
he's sleeping.

34:56.433 --> 34:57.766
And he needed to sleep,
Jude,

34:57.766 --> 34:59.333
you said that yourself.

34:59.333 --> 35:03.300
I mean, it's just,
it's one pacifier.

35:03.300 --> 35:04.633
"Put him to bed at seven."

35:04.633 --> 35:06.300
"Don't give him a pacifier."

35:06.300 --> 35:09.366
These are not hard rules
to follow.

35:09.366 --> 35:11.400
But this, tonight,
is like, you know?

35:11.400 --> 35:14.000
It's like our whole friendship
on repeat for years.

35:14.000 --> 35:15.100
Yeah, and for years,

35:15.100 --> 35:17.066
I've been the screwed up
side-kick

35:17.066 --> 35:19.533
and you're perfect,
Judith winters.

35:19.533 --> 35:21.533
I mean, Jude,
people change.

35:21.533 --> 35:24.166
I'm not the same person
that I was

35:24.166 --> 35:27.333
and neither are you.
I am not a screw up

35:27.333 --> 35:30.700
and you most definitely
are not perfect.

35:34.166 --> 35:35.400
(breathes shakily)

35:37.700 --> 35:40.566
Erica: Thank you.
Keep the change.

35:40.566 --> 35:42.533
Dr. Tom:
Care to sit?

35:44.733 --> 35:47.266
Well, Kai was right.

35:47.266 --> 35:48.400
About what?

35:49.666 --> 35:50.666
(sighs heavily)

35:52.400 --> 35:54.133
Once your friends
have kids?

35:54.133 --> 35:56.600
You're on the way
to friend-divorce.

35:56.600 --> 35:58.666
Oh, well,
that would be a shame.

35:58.666 --> 36:01.166
You and Judith share
a lot of history.

36:01.166 --> 36:05.366
I tried to see where
she was coming from,

36:05.366 --> 36:07.266
to understand her
point of view,

36:09.133 --> 36:11.766
but it wasn't enough.

36:11.766 --> 36:14.133
And that's the trouble
with friendships.

36:14.133 --> 36:16.433
Each one
is a two-way street.

36:17.500 --> 36:20.166
What more can I do?

36:20.166 --> 36:21.333
You can wait.

36:23.300 --> 36:24.433
For what?

36:24.433 --> 36:25.666
(cell phone rings)

36:33.466 --> 36:34.466
(phone rings)

36:35.466 --> 36:37.133
(clears throat)

36:38.166 --> 36:39.100
Hello?

36:40.500 --> 36:42.100
Oh, hey, um...

36:44.066 --> 36:45.466
Can we meet up?

36:45.466 --> 36:46.633
Now?

36:46.633 --> 36:48.166
Judith:
Yeah.

36:48.166 --> 36:50.566
Goblins in 20 minutes?

36:50.566 --> 36:52.300
Please.

36:54.166 --> 36:57.066
Erica:
Sure, I'll see you there.

37:13.066 --> 37:14.400
Um, thank you.

37:14.400 --> 37:15.333
Thanks for dinner,
mom.

37:15.333 --> 37:16.433
Your welcome, sweety.

37:17.733 --> 37:19.200
Sam, wait.

37:22.200 --> 37:24.433
I've been where you are.

37:25.500 --> 37:27.566
In the foyer with lasagna?

37:29.033 --> 37:30.566
I lived your father's life.

37:30.566 --> 37:32.700
And then I lived for you

37:32.700 --> 37:34.733
and for Leo
and for Erica,

37:34.733 --> 37:36.266
never for myself.

37:37.433 --> 37:40.466
What are you talking about,
mom?

37:40.466 --> 37:43.266
Do you really want
to move to London?

37:43.266 --> 37:45.400
It's an amazing opportunity.

37:45.400 --> 37:47.133
For Josh.

37:47.133 --> 37:48.766
But what about you?

37:52.100 --> 37:53.666
Sam, look at me.

37:55.766 --> 37:59.066
I'm just trying to tell you
I know what you're doing

37:59.066 --> 38:00.733
and it's a mistake.

38:03.533 --> 38:04.633
I need to go.

38:04.633 --> 38:07.366
I needed to speak up,
Sam.

38:07.366 --> 38:09.666
And now you need to,
too.

38:14.200 --> 38:16.366
Thank you for dinner.

38:18.166 --> 38:19.100
Sam.

38:28.600 --> 38:30.266
(car door closes)

38:30.266 --> 38:31.500
(exhales emotionally)

38:35.266 --> 38:36.766
(sniffles)

38:36.766 --> 38:39.100
(inhales and exhales shakily)

38:43.633 --> 38:45.633
(inhales and whimpers)

38:45.633 --> 38:47.366
♪ I wanna know ♪

38:51.300 --> 38:53.433
♪ Just how you feel ♪

38:56.766 --> 38:58.766
♪ I wanna know ♪

38:58.766 --> 39:00.066
Thanks for coming here.

39:00.066 --> 39:01.500
Mm-hmm.

39:01.500 --> 39:04.100
I know it's late,
I just...

39:05.633 --> 39:09.033
After you left I started
thinking about what you said.

39:09.033 --> 39:10.566
How I acted and...

39:15.066 --> 39:17.600
I don't know what's
wrong with me.

39:17.600 --> 39:19.266
Jude, you have
a 4-month-old

39:19.266 --> 39:21.000
and you're tired,
and anxious

39:21.000 --> 39:24.066
and the learning curve,
it must be insane.

39:24.066 --> 39:26.566
This is harder
than law school.

39:26.566 --> 39:28.433
I, I can imagine.

39:30.266 --> 39:32.066
And, you know,
I'm trying to be supportive,

39:32.066 --> 39:33.566
but I miss you.

39:35.066 --> 39:36.166
I missed you too.

39:36.166 --> 39:38.500
Everyday there's so many things
that I wanna tell you.

39:38.500 --> 39:40.233
And I wanna hear them.

39:40.233 --> 39:41.400
I do.

39:41.400 --> 39:43.166
I know I got
distracted today,

39:43.166 --> 39:45.300
I do. I just...

39:45.300 --> 39:47.266
It's hard trying to...

39:47.266 --> 39:50.066
Figure out how to pay attention
to a million things at once.

39:50.066 --> 39:51.533
Oh god, I know.

39:55.633 --> 39:58.066
You were telling me
about Ethan.

39:58.066 --> 40:00.033
Oh, Ethan, he's great.

40:00.033 --> 40:02.066
I'm happy,

40:02.066 --> 40:04.400
confused and trying to figure
it all out of course, but...

40:04.400 --> 40:07.266
Basically I'm happy.

40:07.266 --> 40:08.466
And work?

40:09.766 --> 40:14.200
Um, Julianne and Friedken
are sleeping together.

40:16.533 --> 40:19.766
And I got the biggest
title of the year.

40:19.766 --> 40:20.700
No!

40:20.700 --> 40:22.533
I know, I know!
It's crazy, right?

40:22.533 --> 40:24.433
Oh my god,
yeah.

40:24.433 --> 40:27.233
Wow.

40:27.233 --> 40:30.166
Things really have changed,
haven't they?

40:30.166 --> 40:31.766
Yeah, they really have.

40:31.766 --> 40:33.433
For both of us.

40:36.233 --> 40:39.600
Can you handle some brutal
honesty right now?

40:39.600 --> 40:43.500
I never expect anything less
from you, Jude.

40:45.266 --> 40:47.733
I don't feel
like I'm that good

40:47.733 --> 40:50.400
at this whole mother thing.

40:51.733 --> 40:53.233
I'm just...

40:53.233 --> 40:56.700
I'm not used to feeling
like I suck at something.

40:56.700 --> 40:58.233
I know.

40:58.233 --> 41:01.633
And sometimes I really miss
being at work, you know?

41:01.633 --> 41:04.133
Everybody tells me I should
just love being at home,

41:04.133 --> 41:06.766
on mat leave...

41:06.766 --> 41:09.266
I can't tell Aly and Marie
how I'm feeling.

41:09.266 --> 41:12.433
I can't even tell Anthony.

41:12.433 --> 41:15.166
The only person I feel
like I can tell,

41:15.166 --> 41:16.333
is you.

41:24.500 --> 41:26.500
Do you remember those
crazy sex dreams

41:26.500 --> 41:29.233
I used to have about
Professor Lozar?

41:29.233 --> 41:31.333
Mm-hmm.

41:31.333 --> 41:33.566
Well,
sometimes I still have them.

41:33.566 --> 41:35.733
Really?

41:35.733 --> 41:37.233
And I would never
tell anyone.

41:37.233 --> 41:38.500
I can't tell Ethan.

41:38.500 --> 41:42.100
But I tell you because
we tell each other everything.

41:44.000 --> 41:44.533
Yeah.

41:46.700 --> 41:50.600
Erica, I am gonna,
I'm gonna try harder, okay?

41:50.600 --> 41:52.200
Okay.

41:52.200 --> 41:54.000
And I'm wanna make
time for you.

41:54.000 --> 41:56.133
I mean,
I'm gonna make time for you.

41:56.133 --> 41:59.033
I just, things get
so crazy sometimes.

41:59.033 --> 42:01.700
Jude, I get it.
And I'm not gonna get angry

42:01.700 --> 42:04.666
or resentful when you can't,
or you have to cancel.

42:04.666 --> 42:05.733
I promise.

42:07.433 --> 42:08.733
Okay.

42:08.733 --> 42:10.200
Thank you.

42:11.666 --> 42:12.666
I ordered wine.

42:12.666 --> 42:13.733
Okay.

42:13.733 --> 42:14.733
Erica:
When life pulls you apart,

42:14.733 --> 42:17.500
you have to work to stay
close together.

42:17.500 --> 42:19.633
By putting yourself
in each other's shoes,

42:19.633 --> 42:22.266
by reminding each other
of who you were

42:22.266 --> 42:24.400
and who you are becoming.

42:24.400 --> 42:27.766
By remembering that despite
all the changes that come,

42:27.766 --> 42:31.100
there are some things that
will always remain the same.
